name: The Saren
address: Jl. Pantai Nyanyi No.184, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
Place is also just perfect!

The architecture of complex is beautiful, employees are extremely responsive, friendly and helpful.

I‚Äôm glad I stayed at this place and will surely return here. It‚Äôs super quite, clean, free of noise.

At night you can enjoy sounds of nature, despite the fact that sound isolation is just perfect.

Cafe located on the territory of complex is great, coffee is good and I enjoyed every single moment being here. Highly suggest !!! 10 ‚≠êÔ∏è / 10 ‚≠êÔ∏è
review 2: First hotel where I were wakened up by the cleaning staff 3 times in a row at 9am and several times later. Despite my pledge for them to give me time to sleep and do not come to clean the room earlier than 3pm. Overall nice rooms and good lighting. Also, the most expensive laundry I've seen in Bali. Restaurant is nice but not cheap.  Pool is nice! Room is good for romantic trip.
review 3:
Elevated living. Period. This place had amazing rooms with a huge bathtub. Everything about it was comfortable. It‚Äôs right next to a rice patty farm which makes it that much more aesthetic and the quarters of the hotel are beautifully decorated with plants and well trimmed trees. The food also hit different here. Everything is fresh and is made in house. We had breakfast and lunch here and did not regret it.

Staff was also friendly. The only downside was the location of the hotel. It‚Äôs a bit removed but beautiful nonetheless to go for a walk.
review 4: First time staying at The Saren in Tabanan, Bali. Its offer a serene atmosphere, perfect for those seeking tranquility and a break from the hustle and bustle of daily life. The absence of TVs enhances the focus on relaxation and provides guests with a true zen experience. It sounds like an ideal retreat for anyone looking to unwind and find inner peace amidst Bali's natural beauty.
review 5:
We had our stay here for 3 nights, together with my partner here at The Saren and we were left disappointed. The cleanliness of the room was appalling - dirty cups, dead bugs. The overall hygiene standards were far below what we expected, making our experience a little uncomfortable.

Though we did not request for any clean up room service, the staffs would just randomly come in without notice. Not only that, it felt unsettling when one of the staff entered the room while I was in the restroom without any notice beforehand. The clean up room service also felt disorganized as they left our belongings on dirty surfaces.

Overall, we had no issue with the service, the restaurant staffs were lovely. The housekeeping needs more improvement. Location was a little far from the central but would be great for people who wants a peaceful stay.

review 1: I arrived at this villa by sunset and mesmerized by the view, its so enjoyable I forget to take pics üòÖ The facilities is top notch, the building is new and the service is very thoughtful. Coffee maker, sharing kitchen with complete kitchen set. A lot of hang out spaces with sofa and bean bags. The surrounding is really lovely, in the middle of rice field its really quiet. I love this place! üíï
review 2:
i stayed here for 8 days. i had a great time, the aircon was okay. i really like the service! fast respond & helpful. we had an electrical glitch for some moment and the staff gave us a snack bucket, it was really sweet & we appreciate it.

i really love the bathroom, it is very clean & spacious. they also provide smart tv with netflix & youtube.

maybe just be careful of the insects, especially if its raining

overall it was a very pleasant stay & worth the price. will obviously come back again!!
review 3:
Great amenities and great views next to a vast ricefield.Each room has Smart Tv to watch Netflix with and On-suite bathroom. There's a shared kitchen with microwave, coffeemaker, fridge, and anything you need to cook a meal. The pool is great also; they give us some floaties to play with.

There's also a space upstairs to gather around and lounge together, perfect if you want to play board games. Overall a great experience!

If you want Ubud vibes but you're located next to Canggu/Tanah Lot I think this is a prime stay. It's near Nyanyi beach and surrounded by a lot of local restaurants. Great place to spend Nyepi also!

name: Villa Pilou boutique hotel
address: Tanah Lot, Jl. Pantai Nyanyi Gg. Beji No.4, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
We were warmly welcomed by Pilou and his lovely wife Ita and were overwhelmed by the family hospitality we received during our stay. We slept very well in the comfortable bed, made use of the fantastic pool and enjoyed the delicious breakfast with lovely coffee, homemade jams and fresh fruit. (Ita bought extra dragon fruit for us just because we had mentioned in passing that we liked it so much). The conversations with Ita and Pilou were always very nice and amusing, we also received valuable insider tips from Pilou and he arranged an extraordinary and impressive day trip for us with lasting memories. Zen, the house dog, is adorable and always greeted us in a very friendly manner. Next to Villa Pilou there is a great restaurant called Kabunku with fantastic food and a temple where we were able to watch a beautiful ceremony.
We can highly recommend Pilou's villa. It is an oasis of well-being in the countryside with a special charm, away from the tourist centres and at the same time an ideal starting point for various excursions.

name: Sate babi Pak windu
address: Jl. By Pass Tanah Lot, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 2:
So i heard some rumors from my friends, there's a pork satay stall that opens up from 1 - 2 PM afternoon and already closed usually around 6 PM, and it was crowded every time around 5 - 6 pm. Curiously i tried it today around 4 pm while the satay supply still available and try to share my take on this pork satay stall.

1st of all, the pork satay set. It's very straightforward, 8 sticks of satay and " ketupat " for Rp. 10.000 (less than US$ 1). That is a bargain. The taste, the satay is savoury and sweet. Shame the maker can't really serve tender satay, but for me still okay. Even if what i got is straight 2 blocks of lard, it's still taste damn good, tender, smoky, almost melt in your mouth. It also use sambal as the sauce, and it's not spicy sauce too, still enjoyable.
Actually, 8 sticks doesn't fill me up, so i ordered another portion, but just the satay and he gave me 11 sticks. Nice!

Next, the place. It located right before the bridge with white metal, under some tree, across the some soto ayam place.
Have to say it is place in side of a road, so you have to be creative for parking stuff.
Another down side of this stall, it's not that clean too.
Hygiene problems is why i don't give 5 *.

Well i guess it's kinda given for less than a dollar food.

Anyway, 6.5 / 10 . Good for snacking!
review 3: Good, simple and cheap. We went after dark, he almost closing for the day. So location is pretty dark.
